# Official Runtime Lifecycle

This is the flow you should aim for:

```txt id="o7u8rl"
BOOT
↓
LOAD HUNT
↓
REGISTER NODES
↓
INITIALIZE STATE
↓
LOAD START NODE
↓
RENDER NODE
↓
PLAYER ACTION
↓
RUN CONDITIONS
↓
RUN EFFECTS
↓
TRANSITION
↓
UPDATE STATE
↓
RENDER NEXT NODE
```

That is the core gameplay loop.

Everything else becomes layering.

